                <h1>Discover the Origins of Salsa Dance</h1>
                <p>Salsa dance originated in the Caribbean, particularly in Cuba, during the 1920s, influenced by Afro-Cuban rhythms and traditional dances. It gained prominence in the 1960s and 70s, merging styles from Latin American and North American cultures, leading to the vibrant dance form we know today.</p>
